# Vendored JavaScript.
#
# There is no package.json and no build step: these four files are committed as
# they are served. This file is what makes that reviewable — without it an
# upgrade is an opaque binary diff, and a tampered bundle is indistinguishable
# from a legitimate one.
#
# Every version below was established by fetching the upstream artefact and
# comparing hashes, not by reading a version string out of the bundle. Two of
# the four carry no version marker at all.
#
# The sha384 values are also the SRI hashes in web/templates/page.html, and CI
# recomputes them from the files. Changing a bundle without updating both fails
# the build.
#
# To upgrade one:
#   1. curl -sSL <source> -o <file>
#   2. openssl dgst -sha384 -binary <file> | openssl base64 -A
#   3. update the hash here and the integrity= in web/templates/page.html
#   4. go build ./...   (the assets are go:embed'd; a rebuild is required)
#   5. check it in a browser — see CONTRIBUTING.md. A bad integrity value is not
#      a build error: the browser silently refuses to run the script.
#
# The files it describes live in static/files/js/vendor/. This file is here,
# outside that tree, because everything under files/ is go:embed'd and served —
# a manifest in there would ship to every user at /js/vendor/VERSIONS.
#
# format: <file> <package>@<version> <source> <sha384>

