sse.js
    htmx-ext-sse@2.2.3  — PATCHED, see below
    https://unpkg.com/htmx-ext-sse@2.2.3/sse.js
    sha384-QA9wXqexhwzXTuTvuF5QP82pddm3R2hy81UzXi7ioNTqNF2b75hlkkSGjafohhL3
    verified: identical to upstream 2.2.3 except for one line.

    THE PATCH. In swap(), around line 283:

        api.swap(target, content, swapSpec, { contextElement: elt })
                                            ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
        upstream passes only three arguments.

    htmx reads that option to decide *which element's* extension set applies to
    the swap: in its internal swap it does

        const r = g.contextElement ? q(g.contextElement, false) : te()

    — resolve extensions for the given element, or fall back to the default set.
    This app's two SSE regions are `sse-swap="…" hx-swap="morph:innerHTML"`
    (web/templates/page.html), so the morph extension has to be resolved for
    those elements. Do not drop this line when upgrading.

    It arrived with the original vendoring commit (b8850e3) and was recorded
    nowhere until this file existed, which is the reason this file exists. An
    upgrade that drops in the upstream file cleanly would remove it, and the
    symptom would be the torrent list falling back to a plain innerHTML swap —
    no console error, no failing test, just state lost on every tick.

    (Not confirmed in a browser: I established the mechanism from htmx's source,
    not by removing the patch and watching morphing break.)
